Crypt::Rot13 v0.6                               Thu Apr 20 23:03:00 2000
  by Julian Fondren


#-----------------------------------------------------------------------
#-- Basic Installation Instructions:

  perl Makefile.PL
  make
  make test
  make install
  perldoc Crypt::Rot13
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------


#-----------------------------------------------------------------------
#-- Changes for v0.6
The documentation has improved greatly and the version numbering scheme
has been changed.

Since 0.05 was never released, it's changes may also be of interest.
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------


#-----------------------------------------------------------------------
#-- Changes for 0.05 (unreleased)
Most CPAN modules are distributed under the same terms as Perl
itself.  Crypt::Rot13 is not.  See the pod for more information.

There are a number of changes between 0.04 and 0.05, the only
user-visible ones being the changed documentation and a more powerful
rot13 () method.  Legacy code using Crypt::Rot13 will not need
changing.  You can now use any sort of degree, from -INF to +INF, if
Perl can handle it.

The code for the crypt () method has been vastly improved.
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------
